This paper is about adapting neural network language models to new data, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses techniques for improving the efficiency of the adaptation process, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of statistical learning (cs.SD) and neural networks (cs.NE).
